Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_message(25.10)                                          get_message(25.10)

Name
       get_message - Gets the limit, severity, or suppression for a message

Syntax
       get_message

       -help

       -id <msgID>

       {-severity | -limit | -suppress | -count | -short | -long | | -on_error
       | -stop_script_limit | -detail}

       Gets the limit, severity, or suppression for a message.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each get_message parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_message

       -count Returns the number of times this message has  been  issued  this
              session.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -detail
              Returns the message of specified id.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -id <msgID>
              Specifies a single message ID, in the form "ENCFOO-123".

              Data_type: string, required

       -limit Returns the limit for the specified message as an integer. -1 is
              unlimited. 0 is suppressed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -long  Returns  the  long message description, as used for the Descrip-
              tion section in "man <msgID>"

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -on_error
              Returns the error action for the specified message.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -severity
              Returns the severity, error, warn,  info,  or  default,  of  the
              specified message as a string.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -short Returns  the short message description. Equivalent to "help <ms-
              gID>" .

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -stop_script_limit
              Returns the message limit allowed for every public command. Mes-
              sage limit set as -1 means unlimited.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -suppress
              Returns 1 if the message is suppressed, 0 if not suppressed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              * set_message command

